          <p>This lesson opens the door to using other people's pre-written code (modules), and introduces one of the most common data types you'll ever touch — strings. Strings appear in virtually every real program. Understanding their underlying rules (immutability, indexing) will save you from a whole category of frustrating bugs.</p>
