          <h3>WHY THIS LESSON EXISTS</h3>
          <p>Lists are one of Python's most important data structures. Real programs almost always deal with collections of things — student grades, shopping cart items, user records. A list is the container you reach for first when you have a group of related values to store and process.</p>
