      <!-- LIST BASICS -->
      <div class="topic" id="anchor-listbasics">
        <div class="topic-title">
          List basics — creation and access
          <span class="tag tag-key">⭐ Must know</span>
        </div>

        <p>Three defining characteristics of a list: <strong>ordered</strong>, <strong>indexed from 0</strong>, <strong>mutable</strong> (changeable after creation).</p>

        <div class="code-block">
my_list = [<span class="num">1</span>, <span class="str">'two'</span>, <span class="num">3.75</span>]    <span class="cm"># Lists can mix types!</span>
days = [<span class="str">"Mon"</span>, <span class="str">"Tue"</span>, <span class="str">"Wed"</span>]

<span class="cm"># Accessing elements</span>
days[<span class="num">0</span>]      <span class="cm"># "Mon"</span>
days[-<span class="num">1</span>]     <span class="cm"># "Wed" — last element</span>
days[<span class="num">0</span>:<span class="num">2</span>]    <span class="cm"># ["Mon", "Tue"] — slicing works just like strings</span>

<span class="cm"># Modifying — this is the key difference from strings!</span>
days[<span class="num">0</span>] = <span class="str">"Sunday"</span>    <span class="cm"># ✅ Totally fine — lists are mutable</span></div>

        <div class="analogy">
          <span class="analogy-label">💡 REAL-LIFE ANALOGY</span>
          A list is like a row of numbered lockers, starting at 0. Strings are carved in stone (can't change them). Lists are written on a whiteboard — you can erase and rewrite anything, anytime.
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- BUILT-IN FUNCTIONS -->
      <div class="topic" id="anchor-listmethods">
        <div class="topic-title">
          Built-in functions and list methods
          <span class="tag tag-memory">📝 Memorize these</span>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-grid">
          <div class="concept-card"><strong>len(a)</strong><span>Number of elements</span></div>
          <div class="concept-card"><strong>sum(a)</strong><span>Sum of all elements</span></div>
          <div class="concept-card"><strong>min(a) / max(a)</strong><span>Smallest / largest value</span></div>
          <div class="concept-card"><strong>a.append(x)</strong><span>Add x to the end</span></div>
          <div class="concept-card"><strong>a.insert(i, x)</strong><span>Insert x at position i</span></div>
          <div class="concept-card"><strong>a.remove(x)</strong><span>Remove first occurrence of x (ValueError if missing)</span></div>
          <div class="concept-card"><strong>a.pop(i)</strong><span>Remove and return element at index i</span></div>
          <div class="concept-card"><strong>a.count(x)</strong><span>How many times x appears</span></div>
